-- China Copper Consumption May Grow to 8.5 Million Tons in 2015, Zhang Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-02T03:04:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/china-copper-consumption-may-grow-to-8-5-million-tons-in-2015-zhang-says.html
China’s copper consumption may climb
to 8.5 million metric tons in 2015, from 7.5 million tons last
year, as demand increases for home appliances and the country
develops its power grid, Zhang Fengkui, head of nonferrous
metals office at the Ministry of Industry and Information
Technology’s raw materials department, said at a conference
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jarrett Banks at 
 jbanks15@bloomberg.net  